Class InvalidArgumentException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArgumentCannotRemoveAttributeException, ArgumentDoesNotSupportMethodException, ArgumentMissesAttributeException, ArgumentWithoutParentException, BiggerArgumentException, ClosedArgumentException, EmptyArgumentException, EqualArgumentException, FalseArgumentException, InRangeArgumentException, NegativeArgumentException, NonBiggerArgumentException, NonEmptyArgumentException, NonNegativeArgumentException, NonPositiveArgumentException, NonRepresentingArgumentException, NonSmallerArgumentException, NotNullArgumentException, NullArgumentException, OutOfRangeArgumentException, PositiveArgumentException, SmallerArgumentException, TrueArgumentException, UnequalArgumentException, UninstantiableClassException, ZeroArgumentException

    public class InvalidArgumentException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    A InvalidArgumentException is a RuntimeException that is intended to be thrown when an argument is not valid. A InvalidArgumentException stores the name of the argument it was created for. A InvalidArgumentException stores the argument it was created for.
    Author:
    Silvan Wyss
